40|$|With the internationalized step of Taiwan, {{the role}} of expatriates is more important. So my {{research}} wants to discuss key factors of manage expatriates in Taiwan Multinational Corporations and the priority of its key factors. Moreover, my research develops the model of mange expatriates and offers pointers on Taiwan Multinational Corporations. On the first research step, my research used quality research to discuss key factors of mange expatriates. The seven case-study companies were in Taichung. Second, my research used Analytical Hierarchy Process (AHP) in order {{to figure out the}} priority of importance, which subjects were eighteen companies in Taichung. Above two major stages, the result of my research shows:(arrange according to the priority of importance) First: Management Functions. Divide into five times, selection criteria, performance appraisal, training management,compensation and repatriation management. Second: Selection criteria. Including,the professional ability, language ability, international experience and the family support. Third: Performance appraisal. Divide into reaching rate of goal, loyal, life norm, interpersonal relationships and feedback to the parent company. Fourth: Compensation. Divide into the subsidy stationed abroad / <b>extra</b> subsidizing, <b>dividend,</b> basic wages and welfare. Fifth: Training management. Divide into corporate culture and goal, professional training, local acculturation, language training and the second professional ability. Sixth: Repatriation management. Divide into planning futures and develops, expatriate period, repatriation preparation and training. My research developed the key factors which manage expatriates. This management model can help Twain Multinational Corporations arrange expatriates better, reduce fail cost and raise success rate of internationalization. 隨著台灣企業國際化腳步的加速，派外人員的角色益形重要。因此本研究主要探討出台灣多國籍企業管理外派人員之關鍵因素，與其關鍵因素之重要性排序。以發展出管理外派人員之模式，可供為企業做為參考，本研究先以定性分析的方式，針對台中地區七家多國籍企業進行深入探討。結合文獻探討，發展出適合台灣多國籍企業管理外派人員之關鍵因素。並且針對此關鍵因素，利用層級分析法，以台中地區十八家多國籍企業為研究樣本，將其關鍵因素之重要性進行排序。 因此在經由以上兩大階段之研究得以發現，台灣多國籍企業管理外派人員之關鍵因素，與其重要性如下（依照重要性大小排序）： 一、管理功能：分成五大管理功能。甄選標準、績效評估、培訓管理、回任機制與薪資福利。企業在管理外派人員的機制當中，最希望的不外乎是能找到符合企業的文化、適合外派職務的人才，才能避免外派人員失敗的成本。 二、甄選標準：分成性向考量、專業能力、語言能力、國際經驗及家庭支持。其中最為重要的性向考量，包含了是否有適應性、包容性，適合外派到另一個國家的人格特質等等。 三、績效評估：分成目標達成率、忠誠度、整體績效、生活規範、人際關係及回饋母公司。在績效評估中最為重要的是衡量外派人員是否有達到母公司所給予主要的任務與目標。 四、薪資福利：分成駐外津貼／額外補助、紅利、基本薪資及福利。其中給予完善的駐外津貼是目前台灣多國籍企業所重視的。 五、培訓管理：分成母公司企業文化與目標、專業訓練、當地文化適應、語言訓練、培養第二專長。多國籍企業要求當外派人員休假回國時，仍必需回母公司進行培育，以便之後將母公司的文化與目標傳導至子公司的精神裡。 六、回任機制：分成前程規劃與發展、駐外任期、回任訓練與準備。因此，多國籍企業必需給予回任後的外派人員適合的職位與成長的環境 藉由以上本研究所發展出管理外派人員之關鍵因素，可使台灣多國籍企業在管理外派人員上有一定模式可循，降低失敗成本，提高外派成功率，使國際化的擴展更加得心應手。目錄 第一章 緒論 第一節 研究動機 [...] - 01 第二節 研究目的 [...] - 04 第三節 研究流程 [...] - 05 第二章 文獻探討 第一節 甄選標準 [...] - 07 第二節 外派人員 [...] - 10 第三節 甄選標準 [...] - 14 第四節 績效評估 [...] - 16 第五節 薪資福利 [...] - 18 第六節 培訓管理 [...] - 21 第七節 回任機制 [...] - 23 第八節 小結 [...] - 26 第三章 關鍵因素之定性分析 第一節 研究方法 [...] - 29 第二節 訪談過程 [...] - 32 第三節 研究對象 [...] - 33 第四節 訪談內容整理與分析 [...] - 34 第五節 定性分析之研究結果 [...] - 54 第四章 關鍵因素之權重分析 第一節 研究方法 [...] - 58 第二節 研究對象 [...] - 66 第三節 問卷項目編製 [...] - 66 第四節 資料分析 [...] - 70 第五章 結論與建議 第一節 管理外派人員之關鍵因素 [...] - 84 第二節 關鍵因素之重要性排序 [...] - 87 第三節 研究貢獻 [...] - 89 第四節 研究限制與建議 [...] - 91 參考文獻 [...] 93 附錄 [...] 9...|$|R
40|$|This {{dissertation}} {{investigates the}} {{explanations for the}} aggregate corporate activities of stock split and special dividend announcements in the United States (US) listed firms between 1926 and 2008. The study is motivated by the limitation of understanding of {{these two types of}} events, which have previously only been focused at the firm-specific level. Further, by studying stock splits and special dividends, this research seeks to find an answer to the debate regarding explanations of corporate event waves between neoclassical efficiency reasons and modern market-timing hypothesis. The study is also motivated by the lack of a link between the extensively documented January Effect and Halloween Effect in stock markets and corporate practice. In addition to the contribution of the extended dataset provided in this research, the study has examined corporate decisions to announce stock splits and special dividends from a macro-perspective, especially in relation to market-timing opportunities, economic efficiency reasons, and calendar monthly effects. Chapter 1 is the introduction of this dissertation. Chapter 2 provides a comprehensive critical literature review on this topic. Chapter 3 is the research framework, hypothesis development, data and methodology used in this research. Chapter 4 is the initial results of the patterns and frequencies for stock split and special dividend announcements. Chapter 5 first investigates whether market conditions and investor sentiment affect the aggregate activities of stock splits and special dividends. These findings indicate that firms time the market to split shares during bull markets with positive and increasing sentiment to achieve higher abnormal returns. On the other hand, special dividend distributions are more likely to happen in bear markets when sentiment decreases. Firms paying special dividends in bear markets are better performers than their counterparts in bull markets. Chapter 6 then examines whether stock split and special dividend activities are driven by the business cycle. Stock splits are more likely to happen in the economic growth stage rather than in the mature stage. On the contrary, firms tend to distribute <b>extra</b> cash <b>dividends</b> to alleviate agency problems in economic declines when profitable investment opportunities are low. Chapter 7 explores the relationship between the patterns of stock splits and special dividend announcements and the calendar anomalies of the January Effect and the Halloween Effect. Firms are more likely to split shares in January and Halloween period than in other months of a year. However, firms have a commonality to pay special dividends to their shareholders in November and December. Lastly, Chapter 8 assesses which macro-determinant has the strongest explanatorypower on stock splits and special dividend activities, and the results show that the businesscycle effect is the quantitatively strongest along with all the additional and robustness checks. Chapter 9 is the conclusion and remarks of this dissertation, including future research ideas in the related areas...|$|R

